# ğŸš€ Fastrict - Enterprise FastAPI Rate Limiter

**The most powerful, flexible, and production-ready rate limiting system for FastAPI applications.**

Fastrict provides enterprise-grade rate limiting with Redis and in-memory backends, supporting everything from simple API throttling to complex multi-tenant rate limiting strategies.

[![Python 3.8+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.8+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![FastAPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/FastAPI-0.68+-green.svg)](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/)
[![Redis](https://img.shields.io/badge/Redis-4.0+-red.svg)](https://redis.io/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/fastrict.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/fastrict/)
[![Downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/fastrict.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/fastrict/)
[![Performance](https://img.shields.io/badge/Performance-3%2C600%2B%20RPS-brightgreen.svg)](#-performance-benchmarks)
[![Latency](https://img.shields.io/badge/Latency-0.37ms-brightgreen.svg)](#-performance-benchmarks)

## âœ¨ Features

### ğŸ—ï¸ **Dual Architecture Support**
- **ğŸŒ Global Rate Limiting**: Shared limits across all endpoints
- **ğŸ¯ Per-Route Rate Limiting**: Independent limits for each endpoint
- **ğŸ”„ Hybrid Mode**: Mix global and per-route limits in the same application

### ğŸš€ **Extreme Performance**
- **âš¡ Sub-millisecond latency**: Ultra-fast rate limit checks
- **ğŸ“Š 1K-30K concurrent connections**: Enterprise-scale performance
- **ğŸ§® Sliding window algorithm**: Precise rate limiting with Redis sorted sets
- **ğŸ—‘ï¸ Automatic cleanup**: Expired keys removed automatically

### ï¿½ **Advanced Key Extraction**
- **ğŸŒ IP-based limiting**: Traditional client IP throttling
- **ğŸ”‘ Header-based**: API keys, user tokens, custom headers
- **ğŸ“‹ Query parameters**: Rate limit by user ID, tenant, etc.
- **ğŸ“ Form fields**: POST form data extraction
- **ğŸ­ Custom functions**: Complex business logic extraction
- **ğŸ”— Combined keys**: Multi-factor rate limiting (IP + API key + tenant)

### ï¿½ï¸ **Intelligent Bypass System**
- **ğŸ‘‘ Role-based bypass**: Skip limits for admin users
- **ğŸ« Premium tier bypass**: Different limits for paid users
- **ğŸ”§ Maintenance mode**: Conditional bypass during deployments
- **ğŸ¤– Custom logic**: Any business rule for bypass decisions

### ğŸ“Š **Production Monitoring**
- **ğŸ“ˆ Standard HTTP headers**: `X-RateLimit-*` headers
- **ğŸ“± Real-time usage**: Current count, remaining, usage percentage
- **â±ï¸ Retry-After**: Smart retry timing
- **ğŸ“‹ Comprehensive logging**: Structured logs for monitoring
- **ğŸ¯ Usage statistics**: Track rate limit effectiveness

### ğŸ­ **Enterprise Ready**
- **â˜ï¸ Redis Cluster support**: Horizontal scaling
- **ğŸ’¾ Memory fallback**: In-memory storage for development
- **ğŸ”„ Graceful degradation**: Continues working if Redis fails
- **ğŸ”’ Thread-safe**: Concurrent request handling
- **ğŸ§ª 100% test coverage**: Thoroughly tested codebase
- **ğŸ“‹ Clean Architecture**: SOLID principles, easy to extend

