## ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture & Design

Fastrict follows **Clean Architecture** principles:

```
src/fastrict/
â”œâ”€â”€ entities/          # ğŸ›ï¸  Core business models & enums
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ models.py      #     RateLimitStrategy, RateLimitResult
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ enums.py       #     KeyExtractionType, RateLimitMode
â”œâ”€â”€ use_cases/         # ğŸ§   Business logic & orchestration  
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ rate_limit.py  #     Core rate limiting logic
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ key_extraction.py    Key extraction strategies
â”œâ”€â”€ adapters/          # ğŸ”Œ  External integrations
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ redis_repository.py   Redis storage backend
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ memory_repository.py  In-memory storage backend  
â””â”€â”€ frameworks/        # ğŸŒ  FastAPI integration
    â”œâ”€â”€ middleware.py  #     Global rate limiting middleware
    â””â”€â”€ decorator.py   #     @throttle route decorator
```

### ğŸ¯ Design Principles

- **ğŸ”’ Immutable Entities**: Thread-safe by design
- **ğŸ§ª Dependency Injection**: Easy testing and mocking
- **ğŸ”Œ Interface Segregation**: Swap backends seamlessly  
- **ğŸ“¦ Single Responsibility**: Each component has one job
- **ğŸš€ Performance First**: Optimized for high throughput

